<p align="center"><h2><span id="title">Landscape wide statistics</span></h2><img id="icon" src="../icons/icon.png" /></p>

<p><span id="section">Brief Description</span></p>

<p>Converts the whole landscape layer into a matrix and calculates selected statistics</p>

<p><span id="section">Parameters</span></p>
<ul>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Input landscape raster: </span>Needs to be a classified raster to work on</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Statistic: </span>The tool is able to compute the mean, sum, minimum, maximum, standard deviation, lower quantile, median, upper quantile, shannon diversity index, eveness or simpson diversity index.</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Output Table: </span>Output result</p>
	</li>	
</ul>

<p><span id="section">Limitations</span></p>
	<p><ul><li>Only raster band 1 is supported. Furthermore the cells in the raster have to be square. </li>
	<li>Very large raster layers might prevent this tool from running due to memory issues.</li></p></ul>
<br>
<p>
<span id="section">Info</span>
</p>

<p>Martin Jung <b>|</b> <a href="http://conservationecology.wordpress.com/qgis-plugins-and-scripts/lecos-land-cover-statistics/"> LecoS Homepage </a> <b> | </b> <a href="http://hub.qgis.org/projects/lecos">Report Bugs</a></p>

<p><u>Citation:</u> <i>Martin Jung (2012) LecoS - A QGIS plugin to conduct landscape ecology statistics, http://plugins.qgis.org/plugins/LecoS/ </i></p>

